.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp-convert 1  "convert " 
.SH NAME
convert \- Batch\-convert many images (or directories) to WebP, in parallel
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBconvert\fR [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-m\fR|\fB\-\-method\fR] [\fB\-\-lossless\fR] [\fB\-\-lossy\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quality\fR] [\fB\-\-near\-lossless\fR] [\fB\-\-optimize\fR] [\fB\-r\fR|\fB\-\-recursive\fR] [\fB\-\-metadata\fR] [\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-clobber\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIINPUTS\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Batch\-convert many images (or directories) to WebP, in parallel
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Output directory (created outputs are `<stem>.webp`); default: beside input
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-method\fR \fI<METHOD>\fR
Encoder effort (ignored with \-\-optimize) [default: balanced, or from env/config]
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
fast: Fastest: literal + subtract\-green only
.IP \(bu 2
balanced: Balanced (the default): LZ77 + color cache
.IP \(bu 2
best: Smallest: adds Tier 3 forward transforms and meta\-Huffman on top of Balanced
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-lossless\fR
Force lossless (VP8L). The default is source\-derived: JPEG → lossy, else lossless
.TP
\fB\-\-lossy\fR
Encode lossily (VP8) instead of losslessly (VP8L)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quality\fR \fI<QUALITY>\fR
Lossy quality 0\-100 (higher = larger, closer to source); selects \-\-lossy
.TP
\fB\-\-near\-lossless\fR \fI<N>\fR
Near\-lossless preprocessing 0\-100 (lower = stronger; implies lossless)
.TP
\fB\-\-optimize\fR
Try every lossless effort level and keep the smallest output
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
Recurse into subdirectories
.TP
\fB\-\-metadata\fR \fI<METADATA>\fR
Metadata to embed: all,none,icc,exif,xmp (default: all)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
all: Keep ICC, Exif, and XMP
.IP \(bu 2
none: Strip everything (a bare `VP8L` output)
.IP \(bu 2
icc: Keep the ICC color profile
.IP \(bu 2
exif: Keep Exif
.IP \(bu 2
xmp: Keep XMP
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Overwrite an existing output
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-clobber\fR
Skip an input whose `.webp` output exists (still exits 0)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIINPUTS\fR>
Input images and/or directories (PNG/JPEG/GIF/TIFF/BMP/PPM/PAM)
